   <div id="content">
    <div class="story">
     <h2>
     </h2>
     <h2>
      Welcome to CSCS, established in 2004 to provide a structure to:
     </h2>
     <ul>
      <li>
       Foster and coordinate research by faculty and students, and its dissemination within and beyond the University of Chicago
      </li>
      <br/>
      <li>
       Support and develop courses dealing with the various aspects of communication as a phenomenon at all levels of the curriculum;
      </li>
      <br/>
      <li>
       Establish and promote connections with scholars at other centers of communications research and teaching
      </li>
      <br/>
      <li>
       Extend existing interest in communication as an important thematic focus across various relevant units of the University of Chicago, encouraging them to develop communication as a formidable topic of research and teaching;
      </li>
      <br/>
      <li>
       Create and sponsor important public events for the University community and wider audiences that stimulate thinking about communication as a social process;
      </li>
      <br/>
      <li>
       Convey the importance of a social scientific and linguistic approach to communication to larger public.
      </li>
     </ul>
     <p>
     </p>
     <p>
     </p>
     <p>
     </p>
